37905>>>
37905>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37905>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37905>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37905>>>        Case Begin
37905>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37907>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37907>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37907>>>                Case Break
37908>>>                
37908>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37911>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37911>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37911>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37911>>>                Case Break
37912>>>                
37912>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37915>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37915>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37915>>>                Case Break
37916>>>                
37916>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37916>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37916>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37916>>>                  
37916>>>        Case End
37916>>>
37916>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37916>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37916>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37917>>>
37917>>>    End_Procedure
37918>>>
37918>>>End_Object
