38215>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
38215>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
38215>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
38218>>>
38218>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
38218>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
38218>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
38218>>>        Case Begin
38218>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
38220>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
38220>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
38220>>>                Case Break
38221>>>                
38221>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
38224>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
38224>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
38224>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
38224>>>                Case Break
38225>>>                
38225>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
38228>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
38228>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
38228>>>                Case Break
38229>>>                
38229>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
38229>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
38229>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
38229>>>                  
38229>>>        Case End
38229>>>
38229>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
38229>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
38229>>>        Send SetActionButtons
38230>>>
38230>>>    End_Procedure
38231>>>
38231>>>End_Object
