38530>>>
38530>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
38530>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
38530>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
38533>>>
38533>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
38533>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
38533>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
38533>>>        Case Begin
38533>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
38535>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
38535>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
38535>>>                Case Break
38536>>>                
38536>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
38539>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
38539>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
38539>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
38539>>>                Case Break
38540>>>                
38540>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
38543>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
38543>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
38543>>>                Case Break
38544>>>                
38544>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
38544>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
38544>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
38544>>>                  
38544>>>        Case End
38544>>>
38544>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
38544>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
38544>>>        Send SetActionButtons
38545>>>
38545>>>    End_Procedure
